column5: Anyone have any idea, I've checked some of the mushroom websites, no luck.

isnt that the ever elusive shroon that gives you immortality????  seriously good luck on your query.. unfortunatly i only know of two kinds.... 1 comes frome the grocery store 2 comes from the cousin in BC
I don't know what that is, but in my limited experience with mushrooms, if you eat it, you either double in size, or you get a free extra life. Either way, it's a win-win.
LMAO at both Two and Dana's answers!  I can't help you either but one thing seems sure...it's happy to see you!
LOL!!!  I'm shocked nobody has said 'it's a fungi' yet...

It is some type of coral fungus probably from the genus Clavariadelphus. Its tough to judge the size from your photo but the species is probably either ligula or pistillaris. It has also been identified under the genus of Clavaria try a search for either of these names and maybe you will be able to find the one that is closest to the one in your photo.  Good luck!!
...Cliff Claven to the rescue! Gotta love OFC, no matter how obscure the topic, someone around here will have knowledge of it.
From the picture, it kinda looks like it's of the usedcondom variety. HH
The mushroom or fungi is about 2 inches high, 3/4 inch in diameter at the top.  I broke one off, it solid all the way through, no gills.  A quick check, looks most like the one in the linkMy link
I can't get your link to work for some reason Fisherman but it could definitely also be Clavariadelphus truncatus here's a link to some more pics  Mushroom Pics
Yes, thanks for the link that works, definitely the one on your picture, bottom right in the pine needles.
